27/02/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Admiral Michael G. Mullen, commander of NATO's Allied Joint Forces Command in Naples, has praised the progress achieved in Albania's military reform. Meeting with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu in Tirana Friday (25 February), Mullen emphasised that the door is open for Albanian membership in the Alliance, and that NATO would continue to provide the necessary assistance. Moisiu, in turn, commended the NATO and US commitment to the region and the peace and stabilisation process. The two met within the framework of a meeting between army chiefs of the Adriatic Charter states -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia. (Albanian News - 26/02/05; Albanian Presidency Web site - 25/02/05)
